elf":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Complete"}},"components":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/component/12312978","id":"12312978","name":"Core"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Insert  1000 rows into a super column family. Read them back in a loop using multiget_slice. Note leaked file descriptors with lsof:\r\nlsof -p `ps ax | grep [C]assandraDaemon | awk '{print $1}'` | awk '{print $9}' | sort | uniq -c | sort -n | tail -n 5\r\n\r\nLooks like SSTableNamesIterator is never closing the files it creates via the sstable ...?\r\n\r\nThis is similar to CASSANDRA-1178 except for use of multiget_slice instead of get_slice\r\n\r\n","customfield_10010":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_12312026":null,"customfield_12312023":null,"customfield_12312024":null,"attachment":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/attachment/12447042","id":"12447042","filename":"0001-trunk-1188.patch","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mdennis","name":"mdennis","emailAddress":"mdennis at riptano dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matthew F. Dennis","active":true},"created":"2010-06-14T17:17:38.081+0000","size":4824,"mimeType":"text/x-patch","content":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12447042/0001-trunk-1188.patch"}],"customfield_12312340":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"customfield_12312022":null,"customfield_12312341":null,"customfield_12312220":null,"customfield_12310921":null,"customfield_12310920":"92003","summary":"multiget_slice calls do not close files resulting in file descriptor leak","creator":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wr0ngway","name":"wr0ngway","emailAddress":"wr0ngway at yahoo dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matt Conway","active":true},"subtasks":[],"reporter":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wr0ngway","name":"wr0ngway","emailAddress":"wr0ngway at yahoo dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matt Conway","active":true},"customfield_12310291":null,"customfield_12310290":null,"aggregateprogress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"customfield_12311024":null,"customfield_12311420":null,"customfield_12311421":null,"environment":"Ubuntu 10.04","customfield_12311020":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":5,"total":5,"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12466908/comment/12878656","id":"12878656","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wr0ngway","name":"wr0ngway","emailAddress":"wr0ngway at yahoo dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matt Conway","active":true},"body":"I ran my tests against this patch and they pass, looks like this cleared up the leak.  Thanks! \r\n\r\nBTW, oddly enough, my tests never fail (i.e. lsof never balloons up) on OS X even before the fix for CASSANDRA-1178, any ideas why that might be?  I'm guessing implementation details of GC or underlying OS are to blame, but don't know enough to say for sure.  Not important, just curious.\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wr0ngway","name":"wr0ngway","emailAddress":"wr0ngway at yahoo dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matt Conway","active":true},"created":"2010-06-14T17:43:45.145+0000","updated":"2010-06-14T17:43:45.145+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12466908/comment/12878668","id":"12878668","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"body":"committed, with formatting cleanup.\r\n\r\nyes, the jdk declares finalizers on file streams to close them if the GC runs in time; as you note, it's implementation-dependent how often that actually happens.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"created":"2010-06-14T17:58:00.068+0000","updated":"2010-06-14T17:58:00.068+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12466908/comment/12878694","id":"12878694","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mdennis","name":"mdennis","emailAddress":"mdennis at riptano dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matthew F. Dennis","active":true},"body":"not all GC implementations close file descriptors when the objects are collected.  Apparently the one you're using on OSX does.  Curious though, you didn't see *any* ballooning?  If OSX was releasing the descriptors when the objects were collected, I would expect to see a few hundred open files while reading in a loop on OSX and only a handful after the patch.\r\n\r\nrandom thought: It may also be a difference in memmapped IO versus not - perhaps OSX doesn't use it (or isn't configured to)?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mdennis","name":"mdennis","emailAddress":"mdennis at riptano dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matthew F. Dennis","active":true},"created":"2010-06-14T18:44:46.337+0000","updated":"2010-06-14T18:44:46.337+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12466908/comment/12878716","id":"12878716","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wr0ngway","name":"wr0ngway","emailAddress":"wr0ngway at yahoo dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matt Conway","active":true},"body":"I wasn't really watching it while it was running, just checking the count of open files after.\r\n\r\nNo idea about memmapped IO in OS X, I didn't explicitly set anything up w.r.t. it anyway...\r\n\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wr0ngway","name":"wr0ngway","emailAddress":"wr0ngway at yahoo dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Matt Conway","active":true},"created":"2010-06-14T19:49:04.094+0000","updated":"2010-06-14T19:49:04.094+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apac